p%3EIt%20was%20this%20same%20discipline%20and%20care%20that%20led%20my%20mother%20to%20open%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-roth-ira-accounts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20me%20in%20my%20early%2020s.%20Again%2C%20she%20dutifully%20and%20generously%20made%20a%20monthly%20deposit.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20in%20grad%20school%20and%20living%20in%20Brooklyn.%20Sometimes%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20had%20to%20put%20off%20grocery%20shopping%20for%20a%20week%20until%20her%20paycheck%20came%20in.%20I%20regularly%20overdrew%20my%20bank%20account.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-up-for-retirement-struggle-spend-money-change-frugal-mindset-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esaving%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20absurd.%20I%20didn't%20even%20have%20a%20job%20to%20retire%20from.%20I%20never%20would've%20guessed%20that%20account%20would%20change%20the%20course%20of%20a%20life%20%E2%80%94%20only%20not%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22380699f0-2588-4ffd-a23f-4ff76305434c%5C%22%3EMy%20son%20struggled%20with%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20loved%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-mom-at-kids-elementary-school-easier-than-young-mom-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelementary%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20he%20was%20in%20fifth%20grade%2C%20we%20had%20reached%20a%20breaking%20point%20with%20the%20academics.%20Every%20night%2C%20to%20complete%20his%20math%20homework%2C%20I%20would%20pull%20out%20a%20whiteboard%20and%20re-teach%20whatever%20concept%20they%20had%20covered%20in%20class%20that%20day%20before%20we%20even%20began%20the%20worksheet.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20exhausting%20ritual%20that%20led%20to%20slammed%20doors%2C%20shouting%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20tears.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20get%20him%20an%20evaluation%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-embracing-dyslexia-at-work-after-decades-of-hiding-it-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediagnosis%20of%20dyslexia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20learning%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20my%20son%20needed%20a%20different%20educational%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20one%20capable%20of%20meeting%20his%20needs.%20New%20York%20has%20a%20number%20of%20fantastic%20specialized%20schools%20for%20kids%20with%20learning%20disabilities%2C%20but%2C%20like%20all%20that%20glitters%20in%20this%20city%2C%20they%20come%20at%20a%20hefty%20price%20tag.%20Even%20after%20an%20extremely%20generous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fwhat-is-fafsa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20aid%20package%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20were%20still%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20are%20on%20solid%20ground%20financially%2C%20long%20past%20our%20broke%20Brooklyn%20days.%20But%20we%20didn't%20have%20%3Cem%3Ethat%3C%2Fem%3E%20much%20to%20spare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c943635-7093-43eb-b12f-4803199a73ee%5C%22%3EWe%20debated%20moving%20for%20his%20education%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20help%20for%20families%20in%20our%20situation.%20Because%20children%20are%20legally%20entitled%20to%20a%20free%2C%20appropriate%20public%20education%20and%20because%20city%20schools%20often%20lack%20the%20resources%20to%20provide%20the%20services%20they%20need%2C%20parents%20can%20sue%20the%20city%20for%20tuition%20at%20private%20schools.%20But%20the%20process%20isn't%20without%20risk.%20You%20may%20not%20win%20your%20case.%20And%20the%20money%20arrives%20as%20reimbursement%20months%20or%20even%20years%20after%20you've%20already%20paid%20the%20tuition.%20All%20this%20to%20say%2C%20we%20had%20to%20come%20up%20with%20%2430%2C000%20for%20my%20son%20to%20start%206th%20grade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20consulted%20with%20a%20lawyer%20and%20weighed%20our%20options.%20We%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-from-city-to-suburbs-why-ill-stay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20special%20education%20services%20are%20more%20robust.%20We%20could%20take%20out%20a%20loan.%20We%20could%20max%20out%20multiple%20credit%20cards.%20But%20our%20hearts%20were%20in%20the%20city.%20And%20the%20idea%20of%20paying%20interest%20on%20this%20debt%20for%20years%20to%20come%20was%20daunting.%20Because%20when%20the%20money%20came%20in%2C%20it%20would%20go%20toward%20the%20following%20year's%20tuition%2C%20not%20to%20pay%20back%20what%20we%20owed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb56a217-b415-4091-a729-3d1272e82193%5C%22%3EI%20cashed%20out%20my%20retirement%20to%20pay%20for%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20remembered%20the%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20which%20had%20been%20converted%20into%20another%20type%20of%20account%20at%20some%20point.%20It%20had%20about%20%2460%2C000%20in%20it.%20Enough%20for%20two%20years'%20tuition%2C%20by%20which%20point%20we%20hoped%20to%20have%20the%20funds%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20later%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%2C%20who%20has%20always%20been%20better%20with%20finances%20than%20me%2C%20was%20understanding%20when%20I%20explained%20our%20plan.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20do%20what's%20best%20for%20your%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20cashed%20out%20the%20entire%20account%20and%20set%20it%20into%20a%20separate%20checking%20account%20earmarked%20for%20my%20son's%20education.%20We%20started%20making%20monthly%20payments%20to%20the%20school%20that%20spring%2C%20and%20in%20the%20fall%2C%20he%20began%20sixth%20grade.%20There's%20a%20picture%20of%20us%20standing%20on%20the%20corner%20on%20his%20first%20day.%20He%20wanted%20to%20walk%20into%20his%20first%20day%20of%20middle%20school%20on%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20parents%20we%20had%20spoken%20to%20who%20had%20kids%20in%20similar%20schools%20used%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bnight%20and%20day%26quot%3B%20to%20explain%20the%20transition%2C%20and%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20no%20different%20for%20us.%20That%20first%20week%2C%20my%20son%20came%20home%2C%20grabbed%20a%20snack%2C%20and%20completed%20all%20of%20his%20homework%20independently%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20in%20the%2010th%20grade%20now%2C%20preparing%20for%20his%20first%20international%20school%20trip%20and%20thinking%20about%20college.%20And%20he's%20flourishing%2C%20with%20both%20good%20grades%20and%20a%20strong%20group%20of%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reimbursement%20process%20has%20been%20a%20roller%20coaster%20for%20us%2C%20with%20wins%20and%20losses%2C%20and%20we%20have%20accumulated%20more%20debt%20along%20the%20way.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20may%20end%20up%20working%20longer%20than%20I'd%20like%2C%20or%20living%20very%20simply%20after%20I%20retire%2C%20but%20I%20will%20never%20regret%20cashing%20in%20my%20retirement%20to%20help%20my%20son%20find%20his%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcashed-out-retirement-pay-son-school-tuition-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778329981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f3566e3a470d54991e8c83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcashed-out-retirement-pay-son-school-tuition-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20used%20my%20retirement%20savings%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20son's%20specialized%20school.%20It%20wasn't%20easy%2C%20but%20it%20changed%20his%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Marie%20Holmes)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20man%20dies%20in%20US%2C%20family%20says%20he%20battl