%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELeonel%20Garciga%20helped%20implement%20major%20changes%20in%20Army%20tech%2C%20including%20more%20experimentation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELeaders%20are%20pushing%20faster%20adoption%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20%26quot%3Bbreaking%20some%20glass.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Army%20is%20flooding%20the%20force%20with%20new%20technology%20and%20AI%20tools.%20Its%20former%20top%20tech%20official%20says%20rolling%20them%20out%20is%20the%20easy%20part.%20The%20hard%20part%20is%20getting%20soldiers%20and%20the%20institution%20to%20adapt%2C%20a%20lesson%20for%20any%20inflexible%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hardest%20part%20is%20never%20the%20tech%2C%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%20Leonel%20Garciga%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20It's%20getting%20workers%20to%20rethink%20how%20and%20why%20they%20do%20things%2C%20as%20well%20as%20encouraging%20them%20to%20play%20with%20new%20tools%20in%20a%20sandbox%20with%20some%20supervision.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20always%20nervous%20when%20automation%20comes%20in%20or%20when%20technology%20comes%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarciga%2C%20whose%20three-year%20term%20as%20the%20Army's%20chief%20information%20officer%20came%20to%20an%20end%20last%20Friday%2C%20said%20the%20job%20was%20fast-paced%2C%20marked%20by%20efforts%20to%20upend%20decades-old%20processes%20and%20cut%20through%20red%20tape%2C%20allowing%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20more%20space%20to%20experiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20making%20that%20happen%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-betting-ai-tool-get-ammo-supplies-front-line-troops-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epushing%20new%20tools%20out%20fast%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20prioritizing%20user%20experience%20while%20accepting%20the%20risk%20of%20things%20not%20working%20out%20as%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ec6257f-99cb-4365-b534-d0b9610e23b2%5C%22%3E'Let's%20break%20some%20glass'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20kind%20of%20rapid%20change%20Pentagon%20leaders%20are%20now%20pushing%20across%20the%20US%20military%2C%20from%20drones%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-surged-largest-counter-drone-training-mission-middle-east-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-information-overload-battlefield-data-management-ai-tool-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20digital%20tools.%20But%20transforming%20the%20Army%20at%20that%20speed%2C%20especially%20its%20sprawling%20business%20operations%2C%20runs%20contrary%20to%20how%20the%20military%20traditionally%20operates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20sticking%20with%20the%20typical%20yearslong%20development%20processes%20with%20excessive%20deliberations%2C%20Garciga's%20approach%20was%20simpler.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20just%20make%20it%20ubiquitously%20available%20and%20see%20what%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20break%20some%20glass.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20information%20officer%20serves%20as%20Army's%20principal%20advisor%20on%20the%20technology%20that%20makes%20the%20service%20run%2C%20from%20the%20mundane%20software%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20use%20in%20their%20day-to-day%20jobs%20to%20tech%20safety%20oversight.%20It's%20a%20daunting%20role%20because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20service%20and%20how%20much%20work%20has%20to%20happen%20behind%20the%20scenes%20to%20make%20progress%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20you%20have%20to%20have%20this%20mental%20agility%20to%20really%20do%20this%20job%20smartly%20because%20the%20portfolio%20is%20big%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ability%20to%20move%20your%20perspective%20and%20way%20of%20thinking%20across%20different%20areas%20makes%20this%20job%20a%20lot%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20soldiers%20stands%20around%20a%20tablet%20in%20the%20forest.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f8f78a405e0cf89dc86d50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAcquisition%20reform%20in%20the%20Army%20began%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%20and%20has%20accelerated%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20courtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGarciga%20said%20many%20of%20the%20Army's%20biggest%20problems%20came%20down%20to%20user%20experience%3A%20soldiers%20and%20civilian%20employees%20sometimes%20waited%20weeks%20for%20system%20access%20and%20faced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-hopes-ai-can-slash-troops-admin-burden-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esignificant%20paperwork%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20routine%20processes.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20Army%2C%20from%20legal%20to%20medical%2C%20have%20been%20buying%20their%20own%20software%20with%20little%20coordination%20or%20compatibility%20across%20the%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasic%20communication%20tools%20frustrate%20troops.%20The%20Army's%20rigid%20memo%20formats%20were%20designed%20for%20a%20paper-heavy%20bureaucracy%2C%20not%20modern%20digital%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20requests%20from%20soldiers%2C%20Garciga%20said%2C%20was%20help%20turning%20messy%20memos%20into%20documents%20that%20easily%20complied%20with%20Army%20formatting%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22277178b0-bdaa-4575-b7eb-8bb4b8b5f90e%5C%22%3E'Don't%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20process'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnnecessary%20points%20of%20friction%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdefense-prime-contractors-new-problem-dan-driscoll-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebureaucratic%20processes%3C%2Fa%3E%20consume%20time%20and%20eat%20into%20people's%20actual%20jobs%2C%20can%20create%20some%20of%20the%20Army's%20biggest%20workforce%20headaches%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20fixing%20these%20problems%2C%20Garciga%20said%2C%20meant%20pushing%20decisions%20lower%20and%20giving%20commanders%20more%20authority%20to%20make%20calls%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20process%20that%20takes%20time%20and%20delays%20people%20getting%20the%20capability%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20tension%20is%20playing%20out%20with%20the%20Army's%20rapid%20adoption%20of%20AI%20technologies%2C%20which%20has%20unfolded%20more%20quickly%20than%20initially%20expected%2C%20Garciga%20said%2C%20creating%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20whiplash%20as%20workers%20struggle%20to%20keep%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20has%20been%20making%20many%20of%20its%20new%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-making-next-day-fixes-on-new-warfighting-software-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20available%20with%20lower%20barriers%20to%20entry%20so%20that%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20can%20experiment%2C%20but%20dealing%20with%20the%20flood%20of%20new%20tools%20can%20be%20daunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProbably%20the%20biggest%20demand%20signal%20we%20get%20is%2C%20'Hey%2C%20how%20do%20I%20get%20trained%20on%20this%20because%20I%20don't%20understand%20what%20I'm%20looking%20at%3F'%26quot%3B%20Garciga%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20other%20piece%20has%20been%2C%20'How%20do%20we%20keep%20up%20with%20policy%3F'%26quot%3B%20These%20are%20challenges%20not%20unique%20to%20the%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leonel%20Garciga%2C%20the%20US%20Army's%20chief%20information%20officer%2C%20sits%20at%20a%20table%20with%20a%20beige%20suit.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f8f73038bee05c96983986%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarciga%20is%20a%20first-generation%20American%2C%20and%20his%20family%20hails%20from%20Cuba.%3Cp%3ECaleb%20Thompson%2FArmy%20Chief%20Information%20Officer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20Garciga%20described%20is%20a%20prime%20example%20of%20how%20military%20personnel%20and%20civilians%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-agent-openclaw-remy-gemini-assistant-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20corporate%20industries%2C%20are%20adjusting%20to%20the%20benefits%20and%20challenges%20presented%20by%20artificial%20intelligence.%20It's%20changing%20many%20of%20the%20processes%20that%20workers%20are%20accustomed%20to%2C%20making%20some%20bristle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20creates%20obstacles%20to%20getting%20people%20to%20adapt%2C%20which%20Garciga%20called%20the%20biggest%20challenge%2C%20not%20the%20tech%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb325938-c174-4205-af75-7967c8559396%5C%22%3E'How%20do%20we%20push%20that'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGarciga's%20appointment%20to%20CIO%20by%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Army%20Christine%20Wormuth%20and%20his%20time%20in%20the%20job%20came%20after%20decades%20of%2C%20as%20he%20described%2C%20never%20saying%20no%20to%20new%20jobs%20or%20learning%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarciga%20is%20a%20first-generation%20American%2C%20his%20family%20from%20Cuba%2C%20and%20after%20graduating%20high%20school%2C%20he%20enlisted%20in%20the%20Navy%20because%20college%20wasn't%20affordable.%20%26quot%3BNext%20thing%20you%20know%2C%20I'm%20on%20a%20submarine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Garciga%20later%20earned%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-attack-submarine-sends-message-to-foes-stop-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esubmarine%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20pin%20aboard%20the%20Los%20Angeles-class%20USS%20Memphis%20submarine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20early%20proving%20ground%20for%20his%20later%20role%20as%20Army%20CIO%20came%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20when%20he%20helped%20lead%20the%20Joint%20IED%20Defeat%20Organization%2C%20which%20was%20tasked%20with%20rapidly%20getting%20troops%20the%20tools%2C%20weapons%2C%20and%20training%20needed%20to%20counter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-turns-unjammable-drones-into-flying-bombs-ambush-ukrainian-vehicles-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimprovised%20explosive%20devices%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20deadly%20threat%20the%20military%20was%20still%20struggling%20to%20solve.%20He's%20headed%20to%20Booz%20Allen%20Hamilton%20next%20where%20he'll%20serve%20as%20an%20AI%20and%20tech%20advisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20career%20more%20in%20the%20unconstrained%20area%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20War%20and%20the%20intelligence%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20areas%20where%20access%20and%20information%20were%20decentralized%20and%20the%20workforce%20was%20less%20managed%20top%20to%20bottom%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20a%20very%20different%20perspective%20on%20that%2C%20which%20has%20driven%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20policy.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20that%2C%20it's%20been%20really%20focused%20on%2C%20'How%20do%20we%20push%20that%20as%20far%20down%20as%20we%20can%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Garciga%20said%2C%20his%20successor%20will%20have%20to%20test%20how%20much%20expansion%20and%20speed%20is%20tenable%2C%20and%20whether%20there%20are%20certain%20areas%20where%20guardrails%20should%20be%20raised.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20the%20threshold%20that%20we%20have%20to%20put%20some%20governance%20on%20it%2C%20right%3F%20Unbridled%20sprawl%20is%20never%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-pushes-ai-but-getting-troops-to-adapt-is-harder-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20In