20me%20a%20children's%20book%20about%20it.%20He%20set%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20each%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20his%20grandchildren%2C%20which%20is%20how%20my%20investing%20journey%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20hired%20me%20in%202006%2C%20and%20I%20planned%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffire-financial-independece-early-retirement-investing-lifestyle-boredom-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20my%2018%20years%20there%2C%20but%20I%20never%20thought%20I'd%20actually%20do%20it%2C%20because%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20work.%20Plus%2C%20during%20the%202000s%2C%20I%20assumed%20that%20retiring%20early%20was%20only%20for%20the%20lucky%20few%20who%20struck%20it%20rich%20when%20their%20startups%20were%20acquired%20or%20their%20companies%20went%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20I%20developed%20a%20greater%20interest%20in%20investing%2C%20that%20I%20came%20across%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFIRE%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202024%2C%20I'd%20saved%20up%20enough%20to%20feel%20I'd%20be%20financially%20OK%20if%20I%20did%20decide%20to%20leave%2C%20so%20in%20November%202025%2C%20at%20age%2055%2C%20I%20resigned%20and%20entered%20early%20retirement.%20My%20grandfather's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-independence-investing-advice-tips-sp500-retail-investor-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvesting%20advice%3C%2Fa%3E%20helped%20me%20make%20it%20to%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20retiring%20early%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a35f8233-9fb7-499c-a9f6-22be9279ee41%5C%22%3EI%20thought%20long-term%20when%20investing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandfather's%20investing%20philosophy%20shaped%20mine.%20He%20was%20an%20admirer%20of%20John%20Bogle%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20The%20Vanguard%20Group%2C%20who%20wanted%20to%20make%20investing%20more%20accessible%20to%20the%20general%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20advised%20me%20to%20opt%20for%20long-term%20investment%20options%20with%20low%20management%20fees%2C%20so%20I%20could%20keep%20as%20much%20of%20my%20money%20as%20possible%20and%20avoid%20big%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20I'd%20rather%20have%20long-term%20consistency%20than%20wild%20swings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lived%20in%20San%20Francisco%20during%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20of%20the%202000s%2C%20and%20I'd%20often%20hear%20stories%20about%20people%20who%20worked%20at%20companies%20that%20were%20worth%20big%20amounts%20on%20paper.%20My%20grandfather%20was%20always%20skeptical.%20He'd%20say%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EAnything%20can%20happen%20between%20being%20worth%20that%20and%20when%20you%20actually%20need%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%20Some%20of%20that%20came%20true.%20When%20the%20bubble%20burst%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20lost%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cb13daa-1e34-468c-a797-e702d088e0db%5C%22%3ELiving%20within%20my%20means%20helped%20me%20save%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20really%20get%20serious%20about%20investing%20until%20Google%20hired%20me%20in%202006%2C%20where%20great%20benefits%20like%20401(k)%20matching%20encouraged%20it%2C%20and%20the%20high%20compensation%20helped%20me%20to%20save.%20Toward%20the%20end%20of%20my%20time%20there%2C%20I%20was%20making%20just%20under%20%24365%2C000.%20Plus%2C%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falphabet-nvidia-stock-prices-most-valuable-company-googl-nvda-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20options%2C%20which%20were%20definitely%20helpful%20even%20though%20they%20can%20be%20volatile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20stick%20to%20a%20strict%20plan%20for%20how%20much%20to%20invest%20a%20month%2C%20but%20tried%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20market%20opportunities.%20If%20there%20was%20a%20downturn%2C%20I'd%20put%20a%20chunk%20of%20money%20into%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20within%20your%20means%20was%20another%20lesson%20I%20learned%20from%20my%20grandfather.%20He%20didn't%20buy%20fancy%20cars%20or%20houses.%20My%20approach%20was%20to%20budget%20carefully%20and%20not%20spend%20on%20things%20my%20family%20didn't%20need%2C%20so%20that%20I%20never%20ran%20out%20of%20money%20in%20my%20account.%20That%20meant%20that%20if%20a%20market%20opportunity%20came%20along%2C%20I%20could%20allocate%20some%20of%20my%20savings%20toward%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2266433ff9-933b-496b-9d83-e1c96b41cf9a%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20educate%20myself%20on%20early%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20discovered%20FIRE%20and%20learned%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retirees-say-4-percent-rule-overrated-for-fire-retirement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%204%25%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20common%20strategy%20that%20involves%20withdrawing%204%25%20of%20your%20portfolio%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20retirement%20and%20then%20adjusting%20that%20amount%20for%20inflation%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matt%20Lowrie%20is%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20body%20of%20water%20with%20a%20skyline%20view%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fde2b6e1443b8dc48e32df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221701%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELowrie%20used%20the%204%25%2