'm%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20I%20have%20a%20ChatGPT%20scheduled%20thing.%20In%202026%2C%20applying%20for%20jobs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftechnology-broke-job-market-ats-recruiters-hiring-application-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20a%20nightmare%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20is%20to%20apply%20right%20when%20it's%20posted%2C%20so%20you're%20the%20first%20one%20on%20the%20list.%20I%20have%20a%20ChatGPT%20thing%20scheduled%20every%204%20hours%20that%20searches%20the%20web%20for%20obscure%20job%20boards%20and%20finds%20the%20ones%20posted%2015%20minutes%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20project%20recently%20based%20on%20incidental%20learning.%20The%20idea%20is%2C%20if%20you're%20exposed%20to%20something%20repeatedly%20without%20thinking%20about%20it%2C%20you'll%20learn%20it.%20I%20wrote%20an%20app%20to%20replace%20random%20words%20on%20your%20phone%20with%20Spanish%20translations%2C%20so%20you%20can%20learn%20Spanish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20coding%20for%20years%20before%20AI.%20Right%20when%20it%20finally%20clicked%20was%20like%2C%20boom%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineers-on-vibe-coding-ai-tools-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20went%20viral%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%3A%20Did%20I%20learn%20to%20code%20at%20the%20best%20time%20or%20the%20worst%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20feels%20unlimited%20sometimes%3B%20I%20rarely%20hit%20my%20limits.%20I%20feel%20Claude%20is%20a%20lot%20higher%20in%20quality%2C%20but%20the%20tokens%20you%20hit%20really%20fast.%20For%20things%20that%20are%20really%20important%2C%20I%20tend%20to%20use%20Claude.%20ChatGPT%20is%20really%20for%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20running%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-code-token-estimates-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClaude%20tokens%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20on%20the%20plan%20that's%20%2420%20a%20month.%20I%20was%20always%20exploring%20different%20ways%20to%20make%20this%20cheaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20talking%20to%20AI%2C%20you%20sometimes%20find%20yourself%20slipping%20into%20caveman.%20I%20used%20to%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20write%20code.%26quot%3B%20My%20idea%20was%20like%2C%20why%20don't%20we%20skip%20articles%20and%20different%20parts%20of%20speech%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20idea%20was%20baby%20talk%2C%20but%20caveman%20talk%20wrote%20better%2C%20and%20it%20was%20funnier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexander%20Huso's%20Claude%20chat%20is%20pictured.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe1376c9dd4cb81cda897e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22496%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexander%20Huso%20asked%20Claude%20how%20many%20tokens%20he'd%20save%20from%20caveman%20speak.%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Huso%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20I%20was%20using%20it%20to%20break%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-2-white-hat-hackers-became-millionaires-before-the-age-of-25-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebug%20bounties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20ethically%20hack%20something%20with%20permission%2C%20and%20if%20you%20find%20a%20vulnerability%2C%20they'll%20pay%20you%20for%20it.%20They're%20going%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20work%2C%20so%20I%20shouldn't%20expect%20to%20get%20one%20in%20a%20day.%20It%20was%20something%20I%20was%20dabbling%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20dropping%20APK%20files%20into%20Claude%20Code%2C%20and%20being%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BSee%20what%20you%20can%20do%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20I%20mostly%20used%20the%20caveman%20mode%20for%3A%20hacking%20Android%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20not%20gotten%20a%20bug%20bounty%20yet.%20Caveman%20talk%20hurts%20the%20quality%20a%20lot.%20Anytime%20there's%20something%20important%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20use%20it.%20%26quot%3BMe%20write%20code%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20as%20good%20a%20chain-of-thought%20reasoning%20as%20it%20would%20have%20been%20by%20default.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20trust%20it%20to%20write%20any%20serious%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20afterthought%2C%20I%20threw%20it%20on%20Reddit.%20One%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DL29q2LRiMRc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavorite%20YouTubers%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20a%20video%20about%20my%20idea%2C%20which%20messed%20me%20up%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fcheeseonamonkey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMy%20GitHub%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20in%20the%20world%20to%20me.%20If%20I%20died%20tomorrow%2C%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20know%20they%20should%20go%20look%20at%20my%20GitHub%2C%20not%20my%20Facebook%20or%20my%20Reddit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20like%20four%20GitHub%20followers%20out%20of%20the%20whole%20thing.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FJuliusBrussee%2Fcaveman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekid%20from%20the%20Netherlands%3C%2Fa%3E%20blew%20up%20and%20went%20totally%20viral.%20I%20wish%20him%20well.%20There's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20stealing%20in%20open%20source.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20it%2C%20I%20thought%3A%20I%20should%20feel%20validated%20and%20flattered.%20That's%20the%20healthy%20way%20to%20look%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20may%20be%20a%20bit%20eccentric%2C%20and%20my%20family%20thinks%20I'm%20nuts.%20If%20anything%2C%20this%20has%20validated%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20doesn't%20think%20I'm%20crazy%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-caveman-speak-prompt-save-tokens-results-worse-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778319841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider